<hi rend="bold">Quinquagesima, Sunday, February 17</hi><hi rend="bold superscript underline">th</hi><hi rend="bold">, 1901.</hi>
         </p>
         <p>The weather was as unkindly as possible, though there were bursts of sunshine. We started service at 11 a.m. with a smart snow-storm. The <persName xml:id="171">Archbishop</persName> arrived in good time: the following Bishops assisted at the consecration:-</p>
